I . Gi·ªõi thi·ªáu OOP ( object oriented programming ) 
- OOP gi√∫p vi·∫øt code d·ªÖ b·∫£o tr√¨ v√† c√≥ th·ªÉ t√°i s·ª≠ d·ª•ng 
- M√¥ h√¨nh h√≥a th·∫ø gi·ªõi th·ª±c 
- gi·∫£m thi·ªÉu l·ªói v√† c·∫£i thi·ªán l√†m vi·ªác nh√≥m 

1 OOP xoay quanh 4 y·∫øu t·ªë 
 - t√≠nh ƒë√≥ng g√≥i ( Encapsulation )
 - t√≠nh k·∫ø th·ª´a ( Inheritance )
 - t√≠nh ƒëa h√¨nh ( Polymorphism ) 
 - t√≠nh tr·ª´u t∆∞·ª£ng ( Abstraction )

1.1 T√≠nh ƒë√≥ng g√≥i 
+ Hi·ªÉu ƒë∆°n gi·∫£n l√† ƒë√≥ng g√≥i d·ªØ li·ªáu nh·∫±m gi√∫p b·∫£o v·ªá d·ªØ li·ªáu nh·∫°y c·∫£m v√† ch·ªâ c√≥ th·ªÉ g·ªçi l·∫°i b·∫±ng h√†m c·ª• th·ªÉ 
vd  
[
      class BankAccount:
          def __init__(self, owner, balance):
              self.owner = owner
              self.__balance = balance  # D·ªØ li·ªáu ri√™ng t∆∞
      
          def deposit(self, amount):
              self.__balance += amount
              print(f"Deposited {amount}. New balance: {self.__balance}")
      
          def get_balance(self):
              return self.__balance  # Ch·ªâ c√≥ th·ªÉ xem s·ªë d∆∞ qua ph∆∞∆°ng th·ª©c n√†y
      
      # T·∫°o t√†i kho·∫£n ng√¢n h√†ng
      acc = BankAccount("Alice", 1000)
      
      print(acc.get_balance())  # ‚úÖ Output: 1000
      print(acc.__balance)  # ‚ùå L·ªói: Kh√¥ng th·ªÉ truy c·∫≠p tr·ª±c ti·∫øp!      ]

1.2 T√≠nh k·∫ø th·ª´a
+ Cho ph√©p l·ªõp con k·∫ø th·ª´a t·ª´ l·ªõp con ƒë·ªÉ t√°i s·ª≠ d·ª•ng l·∫°i code v√† c√≥ th·ªÉ m·ªü t·ªông th√™m  
+ Class con c√≥ th·ªÉ ghi ƒë√® l√™n class cha n·∫øu c·∫ßn 
vd 
[ 
      class person:
          def __init__(self,name):
              self.name = name
          def introduce(self):
              print(f'my name is {self.name}')
      
      class student(person):
          def __init__(self,name,grade):
              super().__init__(name)
              self.grade = grade
          
          def introduce(self):
              print(f'my name is {self.name} and i am in grade {self.grade}')
      
      P = person('John')
      S = student('Alice', 12)
      
      P.introduce()
      S.introduce()      ]

1.3 T√≠nh ƒëa h√¨nh 
+ Cho ph√©p c√°c ƒë·ªëi t∆∞·ª£ng c·ªßa c√°c l·ªõp kh√°c nhau c√≥ th·ªÉ ƒë∆∞·ª£c x·ª≠ l√Ω th√¥ng qua c√πng m·ªôt giao di·ªán ho·∫∑c ph∆∞∆°ng th·ª©c nh∆∞ng v·ªõi c√°ch th·ª±c thi kh√°c nhau t√πy ƒë·ªëi t∆∞·ª£ng 
vd 
[
      class Bird: # b√†i m·∫´u
          def fly(self):
              print("Chim ƒëang bay...")
      
      class Eagle(Bird):
          def fly(self):
              print("ƒê·∫°i b√†ng bay r·∫•t cao!")
      
      class Penguin(Bird):
          def fly(self):
              print("Chim c√°nh c·ª•t kh√¥ng bi·∫øt bay!")
      
      birds = [Bird(),Eagle(), Penguin()]
      
      for bird in birds:
          bird.fly()      ]

+ Method overriding 
 Ghi ƒë√® ƒë·ªÉ th·ª±c thi theo c√°ch ri√™ng 
[
    # L·ªõp cha
    class Animal:
        def speak(self):
            return "Some sound"
    
    # L·ªõp con k·∫ø th·ª´a t·ª´ Animal
    class Dog(Animal):
        def speak(self):  # Ghi ƒë√® ph∆∞∆°ng th·ª©c speak()
            return "G√¢u g√¢u"
    
    class Cat(Animal):
        def speak(self):  # Ghi ƒë√® ph∆∞∆°ng th·ª©c speak()
            return "Meo meo"
    
    # S·ª≠ d·ª•ng ƒëa h√¨nh
    animals = [Dog(), Cat(), Animal()]
    
    for animal in animals:
        print(animal.speak())   ]  

+ Method overloading ( n·∫°p ch·ªìng ph∆∞∆°ng th·ª©c )
Python kh√¥ng n·∫°p ch·ªìng theo s·ªë l∆∞·ª£ng tham s·ªë , ch·ªâ d√πng tham s·ªë m·∫∑c ƒë·ªãnh ho·∫∑c *arg 

class Math():
   def add(self, a, b, c=0) # c=0 ƒë·ªÉ cho add() nh·∫≠n nhi·ªÅu tham s·ªë 
      return a+b+c
math = Math()

print(math.add(2,4,5)

+Operator overloading ( n·∫°p ch·ªìng to√°n t·ª≠ )
 Cho ph√©p t√°i ƒë·ªãnh nghƒ©a c√°c ho·∫°t ƒë·ªông to√°n t·ª≠ ( +, -, , /, ==, ... ) s·ª≠ d·ª•ng ph∆∞∆°ng th·ª©c ƒë·∫∑c bi·ªát 

üîπ __add__ ‚Üí N·∫°p ch·ªìng to√°n t·ª≠ +
üîπ __sub__ ‚Üí N·∫°p ch·ªìng to√°n t·ª≠ -
üîπ __mul__ ‚Üí N·∫°p ch·ªìng to√°n t·ª≠ *
üîπ __eq__ ‚Üí N·∫°p ch·ªìng to√°n t·ª≠ ==
[
  class Vector():
      def __init__(self,x,y):
          self.x = x
          self.y = y
  
      def __add__(self,other):
          return Vector(self.x + other.x, self.y + other.y)
  
      def __str__(self):
          return f'Vector({self.x},{self.y})'
  
  v1 = Vector(2, 3)
  v2 = Vector(4, 5)
  v3 = v1 + v2 
  
  print(v3)   ]

1.4 T√≠nh tr·ª´u t∆∞·ª£ng
+ Gi√∫p ·∫©n c√°c chi ti·∫øt v√† ch·ªâ hi·ªÉn th·ªã c√°c th√¥ng tin c·∫ßn thi·∫øt 
+ L·ªõp kh√¥ng th·ªÉ t·∫°o ƒë·ªëi t∆∞·ª£ng tr·ª±c ti·∫øp 
+ Ph∆∞∆°ng th·ª©c ch·ªâ c√≥ code khai b√°o v√† kh√¥ng c√≥ th·ª±c thi 
+ Tr∆∞·ªõc khi t·∫°o l·ªõp tr·ª´u t∆∞·ª£ng th√™m 
# from abc import ABC , abstractmethod #
[
   class Animal(ABC):
       @abstractmethod
       def speak(self):
           pass
   
   class dog(Animal):
       def speak(self):
           return 'Bark bark'
   
   class cat(Animal):
       def speak(self):
           return 'Meow meow'
   
   dog = dog()
   cat = cat()
   
   print(dog.speak())
   print(cat.speak())   ]


# b√†i t·∫≠p th√™m 

class Vehicle(ABC):
    @abstractmethod
    def start_engine(self):
        pass

class car(Vehicle):
    def start_engine(self):
        print('car is starting engine')

class motobike(Vehicle):
    def start_engine(self):
        print('motobike is starting engine')

C = car()
M = motobike()

C.start_engine()
M.start_engine()

# cau hoi 
B√†i t·∫≠p 1: Ghi ƒë√® ph∆∞∆°ng th·ª©c
Vi·∫øt m·ªôt l·ªõp Vehicle c√≥ ph∆∞∆°ng th·ª©c move(). T·∫°o hai l·ªõp con Car v√† Boat ghi ƒë√® move() nh∆∞ sau:
Car.move() in ra "Car is driving on the road"
Boat.move() in ra "Boat is sailing on the water"

B√†i t·∫≠p 2: N·∫°p ch·ªìng to√°n t·ª≠
T·∫°o l·ªõp Time ƒë·ªÉ x·ª≠ l√Ω gi·ªù ph√∫t, g·ªìm:
Thu·ªôc t√≠nh hours v√† minutes.
N·∫°p ch·ªìng to√°n t·ª≠ + ƒë·ªÉ c·ªông hai th·ªùi gian.
Hi·ªÉn th·ªã k·∫øt qu·∫£ theo ƒë·ªãnh d·∫°ng "HH:MM"



